Arrays : An array is a data structure consisting of a collection of elements, each identified by at least one array index or key.
An array is stored such that position of each element can be computed from its index by a mathematical formula.
Properties:
-Array can store data of specified type.
-Elements of an array are located in a contiguous.
-Each element of an array has a unique index.
-The size of an array is predefined and cannot be modified.

Types of array:
-one dimensional array.a[i]
-multi dimensional array.

When to use :
- To store multiple variables of same data type.
- Random access.

When To avoid :
-Same data type elements.
-Reserve memory.
